  "title": "Account Admin",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Provide comprehensive accounting and administrative support to ensure accurate financial operations and effective cost management within the organization.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Process accounts receivable and accounts payable transactions, including invoicing and claims, to maintain accurate financial records</li><li>Perform data entry, bookkeeping, and bank reconciliation to ensure financial data integrity and timely reporting</li><li>Manage filing systems, handle email correspondence, and execute general administrative tasks to support office efficiency</li><li>Administer staff payroll, leave claims, and CPF contributions to ensure compliance with statutory requirements</li><li>Monitor accounts receivable and proactively follow up on outstanding payments to optimize cash flow</li><li>Assist in budgeting and cost tracking activities to support financial planning and control</li><li>Execute ad hoc tasks as assigned to contribute to operational effectiveness</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field</li><li>At least 2 years of relevant accounting experience</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Word and Excel for document preparation and data analysis</li><li>Familiarity with accounting software such as Infotech to enhance financial processing efficiency</li><li>Proficiency in English and Mandarin to facilitate effective communication</li></ul>",
